<paragraph blockId="1.[151,598,655,681]" box="[151,598,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,598,655,681]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,598,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1926" box="[412,598,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[412,598,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hoplocheiloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
1. Wing distinctly spotted, transverse bands broken up so the wing appears mostly infuscated, with 7 widely separated, clear, circular patches (
<figureCitation box="[364,423,756,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1829,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-93@7.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hoplocheiloma hispaniola new species. 6, head; 7, male left lateral; 8, male terminalia; 9, female abdomen; 10, spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290091/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Head with only one large seta (inner vertical), other setae reduced or absent (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1236,756,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1829,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-93@7.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hoplocheiloma hispaniola new species. 6, head; 7, male left lateral; 8, male terminalia; 9, female abdomen; 10, spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290091/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2011" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2011" box="[967,1098,785,806]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispaniola" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[967,1098,785,806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. hispaniola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1103,1221,785,806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[1231,1433,785,806]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Wing with a broad discal band crossing middle (
<figureCitation box="[690,762,814,835]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Head with three large setae (inner vertical, orbital and outer vertical, as in 
<figureCitation box="[276,345,844,865]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
)......................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" box="[151,1436,873,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,873,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
2. Notum mostly black, postpronotum contrastingly reddish. Base of oviscape bare and shining dorsomedially (
<figureCitation box="[1268,1338,873,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–21" captionStartId="13.[151,263,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-52@13.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 17–21. Hoplocheiloma maculosum. 17, male terminalia; 18, male abdominal apex, left; 19, male abdomen segments 1–7; 20, spermathecae; 21, female abdominal apex, dorsal. Abbreviations: hy, hypandrium; ea, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; aa, aedeagal apodeme, dp, distiphallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290101/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
)...... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Notum entirely orange to orange-brown, sometimes patterned with silvery grey areas. Pruinose area at base of oviscape surrounding oviscape so there is no dorsomedial shining strip (
<figureCitation box="[797,869,932,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).............................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
3. Wing mostly infuscated, with discal and preapical dark bands separated by clear strips each made up of three more or less coalesced clear circular areas, circular areas usually separated by pigmentation along the wing veins but both clear and dark bands always reaching hind wing margin; apical infuscation distinct (
<figureCitation box="[888,960,1020,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,263,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-38@12.[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Hoplocheiloma maculosum (Loew). 13, live female dorsolateral, Cuba; 14, female, abdomen, thorax, wings; 15, live female anterodorsal, Cuba; 16, head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290097/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Anterior notopleural seta at most half as long as posterior seta. Membranous parts of abdomen mostly pale, female abdomen with pleural pigmentation mostly restricted to bands on dorsal half (
<figureCitation box="[429,499,1078,1099]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,263,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-38@12.[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Hoplocheiloma maculosum (Loew). 13, live female dorsolateral, Cuba; 14, female, abdomen, thorax, wings; 15, live female anterodorsal, Cuba; 16, head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290097/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), male abdomen with pigmentation of segment three circling abdomen and preceded and followed by extensive pale areas........................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Loew)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" box="[935,1153,1108,1129]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosum">
<emphasis box="[935,1073,1108,1129]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. maculosum</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1363,1108,1129]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1373,1427,1108,1129]" name="Cuba" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Cuba</collectingCountry>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Wing bands separated from one another by straight-sided clear strips; dark preapical band parallel-sided, broadly separated from hind margin of wing; apical infuscation indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[768,885,1166,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–12" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1898,1921]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-70@9.[151,1436,193,1877]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 11–12. Hoplocheiloma jamaica new species. 11, female habitus, left lateral; 12, male habitus, left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290095/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
). Notopleural setae equal in size. Abdominal membranes more extensively pigmented, ventral part of abdomen largely dark............................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2011" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2011" box="[1208,1314,1196,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamaica" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1208,1314,1196,1217]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. jamaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1321,1435,1196,1217]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
4. Head and notum orange-brown, presutural part of scutum patterned with silvery grey areas. Wing with three distinct pigmented bands and an infuscated tip, outer margin of discal and preapical bands concave at middle (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1182,1254,1275]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Hind femur dark at least on basal half, with 1–2 orange distal bands.................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson." authorityName="Cresson." box="[858,1085,1284,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perforatum">
<emphasis box="[858,995,1284,1305]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. perforatum</emphasis>
Cresson.
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1291,1284,1305]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
, maybe 
<collectingCountry box="[1371,1432,1284,1305]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Head and notum orange, at least presutural part of scutum without silvery gray pattern. Hind femur usually orange with narrow dark bands (sometimes uniformly orange-brown). Outer margins of discal band convex or more or less straight, preapical band narrow and more or less straight-edged (
<emphasis box="[621,733,1372,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gmelin, 1790:" authorityYear="2850" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[621,729,1372,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="totliana">H. totliana</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[740,810,1372,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1831,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,193,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-96@19.[151,1436,193,1810]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Hoplocheiloma totliana (Gmelin). 31, male terminalia; 32, spermathecae and associated structures; 33, live female dorsal, Cuba; 34, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 35, live female left lateral, Cuba." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290111/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) or coalesced with apical infuscation to form a composite distal band (
<emphasis box="[285,429,1401,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName box="[285,425,1401,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugatum">H. ferrugatum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[435,490,1401,1422]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5. 5A. Hoplocheiloma ferrugatum Hennig female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
)............................................................................. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
5. Wing with discal band sometimes broad but never reaching hind margin of wing, distal band narrow but distinct from apical infuscation (
<figureCitation box="[348,424,1460,1481]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–30" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-217@17.[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–30. Hoplocheiloma rhytisma new species. 27, female habitus, left lateral; 28, spermathecae and associated structures; 29, male abdomen segments 3–7, right lateral; 30, male terminalia, left lateral. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy— hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae (female), pleural sac (male); ss—single spermatheca; gf—genital fork." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290107/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Epicephalon and paracephalon dull, paracephalon not conspicuously bulging. Main vertical row of katepisternal setae usually darker than weaker anterior golden row............................................... 6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Discal band very large, taking up most of wing, broadly reaching hind margin of wing and separated from large apical infuscated area (distal band coalesced with apical infuscation, by a narrow transverse pale area (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1148,1548,1569]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5. 5A. Hoplocheiloma ferrugatum Hennig female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Epicephalon and paracephalon shining, paracephalon conspicuously bulging (
<figureCitation box="[725,788,1577,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5. 5A. Hoplocheiloma ferrugatum Hennig female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Main vertical row of katepisternal setae golden, same color as weaker anterior golden row............................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hennig." authorityName="Hennig." box="[1032,1252,1606,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugatum">
<emphasis box="[1032,1169,1606,1627]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. ferrugatum</emphasis>
Hennig.
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[1257,1330,1606,1627]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1343,1426,1606,1627]" country="Mexico" name="Yucatan" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Yucatan</collectingRegion>
).
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
6. Pleuron with two prominent dark patches covered with silvery pruinosity, one covering the posterior third of the anepisternum and a less distinct one on the upper katepisternum (
<figureCitation box="[720,792,1665,1686]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–30" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-217@17.[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–30. Hoplocheiloma rhytisma new species. 27, female habitus, left lateral; 28, spermathecae and associated structures; 29, male abdomen segments 3–7, right lateral; 30, male terminalia, left lateral. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy— hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae (female), pleural sac (male); ss—single spermatheca; gf—genital fork." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290107/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Discal band more or less circular, widely separated from anterior wing margin and with distal face strongly convex. R 
<subScript attach="both" box="[727,748,1707,1719]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2+3</subScript>
ending far beyond plane of dm-cu (
